Zanzibar President Hussein Ali Mwinyi on Wednesday (March 3,2021) appointed three ministers to various ministries. The appointees Dr. Saada Mkuya Salum will be the Minister of State in the First Vice-President’s Office, Omar Said Shaaban  the Minister of Industry and Trade and Nassor Ahmed Mazrui as the Minister of Health, Community Development, Gender, Elderly and Children. A statement released by the Secretary of the Revolutionary Council, Zena Said stated that their appointment begins effective today and swearing in tomorrow Thursday at 10am. It further noted President, Hussein Ali Mwinyi will also on the same day swear-in  Salum Yussuf Ali as Zanzibar Revenue Board (ZRB) Commissioner who appointed was effected on 10th last month.